        <p>
        <h2><u>Highlights and Tips</u></h2><img class="img2" src="/img/blogs/Samyak-Jain/10.jpg">
        <ul>
            <li>
                Take care of your physical and mental health. Never compromise that at any cost.
            </li>
            <li>
                Earlier you start with clarity of profile in mind, better you prepare.
            </li>
            <li>
                Analyse your performance after every test, learn from mistakes and never mug up the solutions.
            </li>
            <li>
                Keep your placement sem light. I took 5 courses out of which one was modular.
            </li>
            <li>
                The DSA course(ESO207) is a must. I would recommend doing it on campus if you were not able to get it
                then do it from online platforms
            </li>
            <li>
                ML course/ project will be a good add-on to resume. If you were not able to do it on campus(CS771) then
                you can refer to Coursera, udemy etc.
            </li>
            <li>
                Prepare your resume by heart. They can even ask about your hobbies and interests if it is written there.
            </li>
            <li>
                Stay in contact with your close ones including friends, family, etc. Share your feelings with them it
                will help you to deal with stress during the placements
            </li>
            <li>
                Prepare your resume wisely. Don’t spend time on things that you can’t change(like CPI) rather focus on
                making rest of the things impactable
            </li>
            <li>
                Improve your speed in aptitude. It is asked in almost all the tests.
            </li>
            <li>
                Practice mock coding interviews with peers/seniors to avoid messing the real interviews
            </li>
            <li>
                Don’t take HR lightly. It really hurts if you are eliminated at this round. Prepare with at least 2-3
                mocks for this.
            </li>
            <li>
                Give your portal login credentials to 2-3 friends who are not sitting in placements so that they can
                check your portal regularly during interviews.
            </li>
            <li>
                Be consistent in coding. That’s the only way to ace the coding skills
            </li>
            <li>
                Be confident and stay calm. You're gonna do your best!
            </li>
        </ul>
